cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving the performance of semantic image segmentation using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of co-training, which is a semi-supervised learning technique, suggesting that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with medical image datasets, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
